WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:04.870
Alcohol is older than the Great Pyramid at
Giza, Machu Picchu, the Roman

00:00:04.870 --> 00:00:08.940
Colosseum, Taj Mahal and the
Great Wall of China combined. And while

00:00:08.940 --> 00:00:19.689
it's not considered one of the wonders of
the world, maybe it should be.

00:00:19.689 --> 00:00:24.920
Alcohol, or more accurately, ethanol; is a
simple enough chain of carbon and hydrogen

00:00:24.920 --> 00:00:29.519
with an oxygen thrown in for good measure,
but it is most definitely humanity's favorite

00:00:29.519 --> 00:00:35.630
neurotoxin. Anywhere we've been, we make alcohol,
or bring it with us. It's a social lubricant,

00:00:35.630 --> 00:00:41.060
liquid courage, and a constant companion.
It just gets along with us so well!

00:00:41.060 --> 00:00:45.460
When ethanol enters the body some leeches
in through mucous membranes, but the lion's

00:00:45.460 --> 00:00:50.600
share of it travels through the stomach to
the small intestine, to be absorbed into the

00:00:50.600 --> 00:00:54.210
bloodstream. Ethanol is water-soluble, so
once in the bloodstream there's no stopping

00:00:54.210 --> 00:00:58.650
it. Like a drunk Westchester teen it parties
at every stop on the train to drunktown; skin

00:00:58.650 --> 00:01:03.760
and organ tissues, heart muscles, brain cells…
Alcohol pals it up with them all. In the brain,

00:01:03.760 --> 00:01:07.730
it binds with a molecule called glutamate;
a neurotransmitter that normally keeps neurons

00:01:07.730 --> 00:01:12.830
excited so they can fire on all cylinders.
Once bound, your brain slows as your neurons

00:01:12.830 --> 00:01:18.480
become less excited. It also activates GABA
receptors -- the famous GABA molecule is another

00:01:18.480 --> 00:01:22.800
neurotransmitter and needless to say, since
the receptors are active, the brain doesn't

00:01:22.800 --> 00:01:27.400
make more GABA, without GABA, you feel calmer
and sleepy. This continues until the liver

00:01:27.400 --> 00:01:29.520
is able to metabolise it and get it out of
the blood.

00:01:29.520 --> 00:01:35.409
No matter how you get the alcohol in your
body, this long process is how you get drunk.

00:01:35.409 --> 00:01:41.250
Though being human we obviously found new
and horrifying ways to jump the line. Inserting

00:01:41.250 --> 00:01:47.260
drugs into the rectum has been done for millennia,
and was a popular way to take tobacco for

00:01:47.260 --> 00:01:54.850
a while, but still, don't try it. Alcohol
enemas, what the hyped-up media called butt

00:01:54.850 --> 00:02:01.670
chugging, bypasses the body's natural poison
detection and metabolization systems -- getting

00:02:01.670 --> 00:02:07.159
people WAY too drunk WAY too fast. It's super
dangerous. Alcohol inserted into the body

00:02:07.159 --> 00:02:12.140
via an alcohol enema isn't processed by the
digestive system and can cause alcohol poisoning,

00:02:12.140 --> 00:02:18.370
and even death. Not to mention if you DO live,
you can have anal pain, tenesmus -- or the

00:02:18.370 --> 00:02:23.530
feeling to GO a lot, and colonic bleeding.
Vodka-soaked tampons are along this same vein

00:02:23.530 --> 00:02:27.980
(no pun intended) with the mucosal membranes
becoming irritated and burning from alcohol

00:02:27.980 --> 00:02:28.340
contact.

00:02:28.340 --> 00:02:34.130
But that doesn't stop people from trying things,
OHHHHH no. Palcohol is a powder-like alcohol

00:02:34.130 --> 00:02:39.500
legalized in the U.S. in March of 2015, and
then banned in some places shortly thereafter.

00:02:39.500 --> 00:02:43.740
We talked about it on DNews, remember? No?
Come subscribe so you don't miss it for next

