description by the VICE reporter should too.

00:03:17.370 --> 00:03:22.819
Ouch. But ,if you're trying to get to the
blood, why not go right to the source? Cause

00:03:22.819 --> 00:03:23.720
some people do.

00:03:23.720 --> 00:03:29.550
A 1999 Oxford Journal study looked into people
who injected alcohol directly into their bloodstream,

00:03:29.550 --> 00:03:33.879
and although they didn't die, there was burning
pain. Three case studies looked at people

00:03:33.879 --> 00:03:39.599
who admitted to injecting vodka, sherry, whiskey,
and one guy even tried beer. But they weren't

00:03:39.599 --> 00:03:45.069
the first. Victorians were famous for gettin'
crunk. A man named H.C. Dalton injected whiskey

00:03:45.069 --> 00:03:49.709
-- not ethanol mind you, whiskey -- under
the skin of patients suffering from morphine

00:03:49.709 --> 00:03:55.019
poisoning. This guy was mixing a deadly cocktail
for sure. Of course, he wasn't trying to get

00:03:55.019 --> 00:04:00.050
the man drunk; it wasn't his first rodeo;
he'd used whiskey injections in the past to

00:04:00.050 --> 00:04:04.610
keep patients alive and kicking. Funny story,
this was all described by the 1911 Montreal

00:04:04.610 --> 00:04:09.300
Medical Journal, and alcohol was listed as
a stimulant (but it's not. It's a depressant).

00:04:09.300 --> 00:04:12.459
Gives a whole new meaning to "doing a shot,"
doesn't it?

